<body>

<header>
    <h1>Gesture Based Artificial Intelligence System for Paralysed Persons</h1>
    <p>Assistive Technology Using Hand Gesture Recognition</p>
</header>

<section>
    <h2>Abstract</h2>
    <p>
        Paralysis affects the ability of a person to move or communicate normally.
        Many paralysed persons depend on others for daily activities.
        This project presents a Gesture Based Artificial Intelligence system
        that helps paralysed persons interact with machines using hand gestures.
        A camera captures the hand movement, computer vision techniques identify
        the gesture, and AI logic converts it into meaningful actions such as
        wheelchair movement, alert message, or device control.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        Communication and mobility are major challenges faced by paralysed persons.
        Traditional input methods such as switches, keyboards, and voice commands
        are not suitable for everyone. Gesture based interaction provides a
        touch-free and natural way of communication. With the help of Artificial
        Intelligence and Computer Vision, hand gestures can be detected and
        recognized accurately in real time.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>To assist paralysed persons using gesture recognition</li>
        <li>To provide communication without speech</li>
        <li>To reduce dependency on caretakers</li>
        <li>To use Artificial Intelligence for gesture interpretation</li>
        <li>To design a low cost assistive system</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Existing System</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Manual wheelchairs</li>
        <li>Button based control systems</li>
        <li>Voice controlled devices</li>
        <li>High dependency on caretakers</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Proposed System</h2>
    <p>
        The proposed system uses a camera to capture hand gestures.
        The captured images are processed using computer vision techniques.
        Hand landmarks are detected and gestures are recognized.
        Based on the recognized gesture, actions such as movement or alert
        are executed.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>System Architecture</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Camera Input</li>
        <li>Image Processing</li>
        <li>Hand Landmark Detection</li>
        <li>Gesture Recognition</li>
        <li>AI Decision Making</li>
        <li>Action Execution</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Hardware Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Web Camera</li>
        <li>Computer or Laptop</li>
        <li>Arduino (optional)</li>
        <li>Motor Driver (optional)</li>
        <li>Wheelchair Motors (optional)</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Software Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>HTML</li>
        <li>CSS</li>
        <li>Python</li>
        <li>OpenCV</li>
        <li>MediaPipe</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Applications</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Gesture controlled wheelchair</li>
        <li>Hospital patient alert system</li>
        <li>Smart home automation</li>
        <li>Emergency communication system</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Future Enhancements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Machine learning based gesture classification</li>
        <li>Mobile application integration</li>
        <li>Voice and gesture combined system</li>
        <li>IoT based smart control</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
        The Gesture Based Artificial Intelligence System provides an effective
        solution for assisting paralysed persons. It improves independence,
        communication, and quality of life. The system is simple, accurate,
        and affordable, making it suitable for real world applications.
    </p>
</section>

